31. Financial risk management (continued)

(a) Market risk

(1')

Currency risk

The Group operates in a number of countries with dominant operations in Singapore, Malaysia, Cambodia, Indonesia and the People's Republic of China. Sale and purchase transactions between the companies in the Group are mainly denominated in Singapore Dollar.

Whenever possible, in their respective dealings with non-related parties, the companies in the Group would use their respective functional currencies, to minimise foreign currency risk.

Currently, the Group will try to manage its currency exposures by having natural hedges between its foreign currency receivables and payables; and/or entering into currency forwards with banks.
